public class Member extends Object implements Comparable<Member>
The Member class creates a Member using member(user) data and does various manipulations with members.

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Member member)
      Compares two members and returns their precedence based on their names. If last names are the same, returns the precedence of the first names through helperCompareTo. If firstnames are the same, returns precedence of the last names through helperCompareTo.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Member>
      Parameters:
      member - A Member object that will be compared with another Member.
      Returns:
      helperCompareTo(this.lname, member.lname) if two members first name are not the same.

    • membershipFee

      public double membershipFee()
      Computes the membership fee for the member.
      Returns:
      oneTimeFee + (monthlyFee * numMonths) the computation for the membership fee for a standard membership.

    • helperCompareTo

      private int helperCompareTo(String thisName, String memberName)
      Compares two members first names or last names and returns their precedence.
      Parameters:
      thisName - name of the first Member that is doing the comparing.
      memberName - name of the second Member that is being compared.
      Returns:
      1 if member name that is doing the comparing is larger than the member name that it is being compared with.
